claim.claim-text:
13. A carrier structure operative to support an electronic device and being rearwardly insertable therewith into a housing structure to a supported operating position therein, the electronic device having a portion which, during operation of the device, is rotationally driven about an axis and tends to create in the device oscillatory rotational vibration about said axis, said carrier structure comprising: 
front and rear end portions spaced apart in a first direction; 
first and second opposite side portions extending in said first direction between said front and rear portions and being spaced apart from one another in a second direction transverse to said first direction; 
a fastening portion operative to anchor the electronic device to said carrier structure in an orientation in which said axis is generally transverse to said first and second directions and position at a predetermined axis location on said carrier structure; and 
a vibration control portion offset in said first direction from said axis location and operative, in response to rearward insertion of said carrier structure into the housing structure to said supported operating position therein, to create opposing interference fits between the inserted carrier structure and the housing structure which substantially inhibit vibratory oscillation of said carrier structure about said axis of the secured electronic device.

23. A computer system comprising a CPU unit having a microprocessor and a data storage section operative to store data retrievable by said microprocessor, said data storage section comprising: 
a housing structure; 
a data storage device which, during operation thereof, generates oscillatory rotational vibrational forces therein about an axis of said data storage device; 
a carrier structure including: 
a body removably insertable into said housing structure to a supported operating position therein; 
a fastening structure for anchoring said data storage device to said body for insertion therewith into said housing structure; and 
a vibration control structure associated with said body and operative to create between said housing structure and the inserted body spaced apart interference fits that substantially inhibit rotational vibratory oscillation of the inserted body, and thus said data storage device, relative to said housing structure about said axis.
